"title": "7730: explanation",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "7730: explanation",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The provision of the understanding of a dream, vision, parable, teaching or other matter, the meaning of which is less than obvious.</p>\n<h2>Examples of the explanation of dreams</h2>\n<h3>By Joseph</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen40:6-Gen40:19\">GEN 40:6–40:19</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen41:10-Gen41:32\">GEN 41:10–41:32</a></p>\n<h3>By Daniel</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:16\">DAN 2:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:24\">DAN 2:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan2:27-Dan2:45\">DAN 2:27–2:45</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:12\">DAN 5:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan5:17\">DAN 5:17</a></p>\n<h3>By angels</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:15-Dan7:18\">DAN 7:15–7:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan7:23-Dan7:27\">DAN 7:23–7:27</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of the explanation of visions</h2>\n<h3>By Gabriel</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan8:15-Dan8:16\">DAN 8:15–8:16</a></strong></p>\n<h3>By an angel</h3>\n<p><em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:8-Zech1:10\">ZEC 1:8–1:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech1:18-Zech1:21\">ZEC 1:18–1:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:3-Rev17:7\">REV 17:3–17:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev17:18\">REV 17:18</a></p>\n<h3>By Peter</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:4-Acts11:17\">ACT 11:4–11:17</a></p>\n<h2>Jesus Christ gave his disciples explanations</h2>\n<h3>Of his parables</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:34\">MRK 4:34</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt15:15-Matt15:20\">MAT 15:15–15:20</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark7:17-Mark7:23\">MRK 7:17–7:23</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:36-Matt13:43\">MAT 13:36–13:43</a></p>\n<h3>Of the Scriptures referring to himself and his relationship to his Father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke24:27\">LUK 24:27</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:25\">JHN 16:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John16:29-John16:30\">JHN 16:29–16:30</a></p>\n<h3>Of his suffering, death and resurrection</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21\">MAT 16:21</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31\">MRK 8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:22\">LUK 9:22</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John4:25-John4:26\">JHN 4:25–4:26</a></p>\n<h2>The gospel was explained</h2>\n<p>By Peter, at Pentecost:\n <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:14\">ACT 2:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:16\">ACT 2:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:30-Acts8:31\">ACT 8:30–8:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts8:34-Acts8:35\">ACT 8:34–8:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts17:2-Acts17:3\">ACT 17:2–17:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts28:23\">ACT 28:23</a>; \n<a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts18:24-Acts18:26\">ACT 18:24–18:26</a> <em>by Aquila and Priscilla</em></p>\n<h2>Examples of other explanations</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg14:12-Judg14:17\">JDG 14:12–14:17</a> <em>The Philistines desperately wanted the answer to Samson's riddle.</em>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam8:9\">1SA 8:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam10:25\">1SA 10:25</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs4:29-1Kgs4:34\">1KI 4:29–4:34</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Kgs10:1-1Kgs10:3\">1KI 10:1–10:3</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Chr9:1-2Chr9:2\">2CH 9:1–9:2</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Neh8:7-Neh8:8\">NEH 8:7–8:8</a></p>",
